# Snake Game 🐍

![Gameplay](assets/snake-gameplay.png)

A classic Snake game written in Python using the Turtle graphics library.

## Features

* WASD controls
* Random food spawning
* Score tracking
* Highscore persistence
* Snake growth after eating food
* Collision detection with walls and tail
* Dynamic color and background change after reaching a score of 5

## Technologies

* Python 3
* Turtle
* Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)

## Project Structure

```text
main.py          # Main game loop
snake.py         # Snake class and movement logic
food.py          # Food generation
scoreboard.py    # Score and highscore handling
highscore.txt    # Highscore storage
```

## How to Run

1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/brunomaruwka1/snake-game-python.git
```

2. Navigate to the project directory

```bash
cd snake-game-python
```

3. Run the game

```bash
python main.py
```

## What I Learned

* Object-oriented programming in Python
* Working with multiple modules
* Event handling and keyboard input
* File operations (saving and loading highscores)
* Game loop implementation
* Collision detection

